<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0">
        <title>Docs for Health</title>
        <link
            rel="stylesheet"
            href="<%=htmlWebpackPlugin.files.chunks.main.css %>"
        />
    </head>
    <body>
        <nav class="nav">
            <div class="nav__contents">
                <a href="#">
                    <img
                        class="nav__logo"
                        src="assets/images/logo-with-text.png"
                        alt="Docs for Health logo"
                    />
                </a>
                <button type="button" class="nav__menu-toggle"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="nav__links-container">
                <ul class="nav__links">
                    <li>
                        <a class="nav__link" href="#">Resources</a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a class="nav__link" href="#">Toolkits</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </nav>
        <header class="landing-header">
            <div class="landing-header__container">
                <h1 class="heading heading--1">
                    Provider resources for the determinants of health
                </h1>
                <p class="text text--large margin-b-3">
                    Helping healthcare providers create a system that truly
                    supports our vulnerable patients
                </p>
                <div class="button-container">
                    <button type="button" class="button-container__button button">
                        Show me the resources
                    </button>
                    <button type="button" class="button-container__button button button--outline">
                        Get in touch
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>
        <section class="landing-video">
            <div class="landing-video__description">
                <h2 class="heading heading--3">Why Docs for Health?</h2>
                <p class="text">
                    Ask Megan, an outreach program manager who helped put
                    together Docs for Health
                </p>
            </div>
            <img
                class="landing-video__preview"
                src="assets/images/picture-megan.png"
                alt="Megan Smith headshot"
            />
            <button
                type="button"
                class="landing-video__button"
                aria-label="Play introductory video"
            ></button>
        </section>
        <section class="landing-cover-video-overflow">
            <div class="landing-mission">
                <h2 class="landing-mission__title">Our mission</h2>
                <p class="text">
                    Providers use Docs for Health to support patients in
                    accessing the insufficient resources that exist within our
                    current system of care. The resources here are valuable and
                    possibly life-changing, but they are
                    <strong>
                        the start of, not an end to, our collective work to
                        create a system that truly supports our vulnerable
                        patients.
                    </strong>
                    Our mission is twofold:
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="landing-values">
                <div
                    class="landing-values__value landing-values__value--reversed"
                >
                    <div class="landing-values__value__description">
                        <h3 class="landing-values__value__description-title heading heading--2">
                            <span class="heading__subtitle">Improve</span>
                            <span class="heading__title"
                                >Patient quality of life</span
                            >
                            <span class="heading__subtitle">and outcomes</span>
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text">
                            Paperwork alone will never lead to justice but it is
                            a place to start. We will raise awareness of the
                            consequences of our needs- and deficits-based
                            systems of care by equipping providers with
                            practical knowledge to support productive
                            partnerships with patients.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="landing-values__value__image">
                        <img
                            src="assets/images/illustration-flower.png"
                            alt="Illustration of flower to represent quality of life"
                        />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="landing-values__value">
                    <div class="landing-values__value__description">
                        <h3 class="landing-values__value__description-title heading heading--2">
                            <span class="heading__subtitle">Promote a</span>
                            <span class="heading__title"
                                >Rights-based approach</span
                            >
                            <span class="heading__subtitle"
                                >to patient care</span
                            >
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text">
                            By making visible the ways our patients experience
                            structural violence, Docs for Health contributes to
                            the dialogue about the state of our healthcare and
                            social service systems, where patients and providers
                            exist within them, and how we collectively navigate
                            them.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="landing-values__value__image">
                        <img
                            src="assets/images/illustration-scale.png"
                            alt="Illustration of scale to represent a rights-based approach"
                        />
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="landing-categories">
            <div id="landing-categories-nav"
                class="landing-categories__nav">
                <button type="button"
                    class="landing-categories__nav__arrow landing-categories__nav__arrow--back"></button>
                <ul class="landing-categories__nav__items">
                    <% for (let index in categories) { %>
                        <li class="landing-categories__nav__item"
                            data-slick-nav-target-id="landing-categories"
                            data-slick-nav-target-index="<%= index %>"
                        >
                            <button
                                type="button"
                                class="landing-categories__nav__item__control"
                            >
                                <%= categories[index] %>
                            </button>
                        </li>
                    <% } %>
                </ul>
                <button type="button" class="landing-categories__nav__arrow"></button>
            </div>
            <div id="landing-categories"
                class="landing-categories__slide-container"
                data-slick-active-class="landing-categories__nav__item--active"
                data-slick='<%= JSON.stringify({
                    adaptiveHeight: true,
                    arrows: true,
                    prevArrow: "#landing-categories-nav .landing-categories__nav__arrow--back",
                    nextArrow: "#landing-categories-nav .landing-categories__nav__arrow",
                }) %>'
            >
                <% for (let category of categories) { %>
                    <div><div class="landing-categories__slide">
                        <div class="landing-categories__slide__description">
                            <h3 class="heading heading--2">
                                <span class="heading__title">
                                    <%= category %>
                                </span>
                            </h3>
                            <p class="text margin-b-2">
                                Safe housing provides a stable foundation for patients
                                to work on health-related goals. Without adequate
                                housing, patients may be too preoccupied with survival
                                to discuss longer-term health concerns. For patients
                                with housing, ensuring that living arrangements are
                                sensitive to health-related needs can be an ongoing
                                challenge.
                            </p>
                            <div class="button-container">
                                <button type="button" class="button-container__button button button--outline">
                                    View all resources
                                </button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <ul class="landing-categories__slide__examples">
                            <li class="landing-categories__slide__example">
                                <h4 class="heading heading--3">
                                    <a href="#" class="link"
                                        >Reasonable accommodation request</a
                                    >
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text">
                                    Helps individual counter disability-related denials
                                    and evictions and advocate for necessary repairs
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="landing-categories__slide__example">
                                <h4 class="heading heading--3">
                                    <a href="#" class="link"
                                        >Emotional support animal</a
                                    >
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text">
                                    Allows an individual to bring an animal into a
                                    building (or other place) that prohibits pets,
                                    and/or waives a pet deposit fee
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li class="landing-categories__slide__example">
                                <h4 class="heading heading--3">
                                    <a href="#" class="link"
                                        >Prevention of utilities shut-off</a
                                    >
                                </h4>
                                <p class="text">
                                    Prevents utilities shut-offs for individuals who are
                                    seriously ill or handicapped
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div></div>
                <% } %>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="landing-toolkits">
            <div class="landing-toolkits__featured">
                <h3 class="heading heading--2">
                    <span class="heading__subtitle">Explore our</span>
                    <span class="heading__title">Buprenorphine Toolkit</span>
                </h3>
                <p class="text margin-b-2">
                    From receiving a buprenorphine waiver to prescribing
                    buprenorphine on the ground, the Buprenorphine Toolkit
                    supports those new to prescribing buprenorphine with short
                    video demonstrations of the knowledge and tools necessary
                    for every step of buprenorphine use in a clinical setting.
                </p>
                <div class="button-container">
                    <button type="button" class="button-container__button button">
                        Access this toolkit
                    </button>
                    <button type="button" class="button-container__button button button--outline">
                        View all toolkits
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        <section class="landing-contact">
            <div class="landing-contact__form">
                <h3 class="heading heading--2">
                    <span class="heading__title">Get in touch</span>
                </h3>
                <p class="text margin-b-2">
                    Feedback on our resources? Thoughts on how to create a
                    system that is sustainable and empowering both for our
                    patients and for us as providers? Send us a message.
                </p>
                <form class="form margin-b-2" action="">
                    <div class="form__item form__item--half">
                        <label class="form__text" for="contact-name">Your name</label>
                        <input
                            class="form__control"
                            id="contact-name"
                            type="text"
                            placeholder="What is your name?"
                            required
                        />
                    </div>
                    <div class="form__item form__item--half">
                        <label class="form__text" for="contact-email">Your email</label>
                        <input
                            class="form__control"
                            id="contact-email"
                            type="text"
                            placeholder="How can we get back to you?"
                            required
                        />
                    </div>
                    <div class="form__item">
                        <label class="form__text" for="contact-message">Your message</label>
                        <textarea
                            class="form__control"
                            id="contact-message"
                            cols="30"
                            rows="10"
                            placeholder="What comments, suggestions, or feedback do you have?"
                            required
                        ></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <!-- <div class="form__item text-center">
                        <button type="submit" class="button button--outline">Send your message</button>
                    </div> -->
                </form>
                <p class="text text-center">
                    Or email us directly at
                    <br>
                    <a class="link" href="mailto:community@docsforhealth.org"
                        >community@docsforhealth.org</a
                    >
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <footer class="footer">
            <div class="footer__content">
                <img
                    class="footer__logo"
                    src="assets/images/logo-with-text.png"
                    alt="Docs for Health logo"
                />
                <ul class="footer__links">
                    <li class="footer__link">
                        <a class="link" href="#">Privacy policy</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="footer__link">
                        <a class="link" href="#">Terms of service</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="footer__content">
                <p class="text">
                    Docs for Health is a free community resource developed and
                    maintained by the
                    <a class="link" href="#">Social Medicine Collaborative</a>
                    in Providence, RI.
                </p>
                <p class="text">
                    While every resource is thoroughly researched and vetted,
                    all resources are provided “as is” without warranty of any
                    kind. Use at your own risk.
                </p>
            </div>
        </footer>
        <script src="<%= htmlWebpackPlugin.files.chunks.main.entry %>"></script>
    </body>
</html>
